8:
I wonder if Marina's doing well... Does
she even remember who I am?
18:
What's up? Did you forget to deliver
something, or?
21:
Oh, no. I just got the feeling that
someone was calling out to me.
Maybe it was just in my head.
24:
But I can't meet Marina now, not
when I'm in this in sorry state...
30:
Luca, are you okay? Did something
strange happen again?
32: No, mom. I'm okay. Thanks for asking.
35:
Say, Luca... Maybe you should go
and talk to those people you
mentioned. Get their advice.
38:
I knew it!
It was you!
46:
What a surprise, Luca! To think that
this is the Float you lived on!
49:
Yes, I also didn't expect to meet all
of you here.
62:
Were you really able to hear me? In
your head, I mean.
66:
...Yes. Now that I think about it,
something similar happened before,
didn't it?
79:
I've been hypothesizing about that...
It may be because of the drugs that
Adala forced me to drink.
82:
My body's felt fine otherwise, but...
strange things keep happening. I
keep communicating with people
and animals.
85:
...And sometimes things start
moving... on their own.
95:
I can tell it scares my mother, so I
want to do something about it, but...
98:
Sounds like telepathy and
telekenesis. You probably have
awakened powers.
102:
You've heard of this condition
before?!
106:
Yeah, I recently met a bunch of
people like that. Well, I was reunited
with some of them, technically. It's
complicated.
110:
Luca... If you wouldn't mind, would
you accompany us to our base of
operations? We might be able to
help you control this power.
120: Of course. You're welcome to join us.
124:
I... I'm very grateful for your
consideration, but... I don't want to
cause you any more trouble—
127:
Sorry to butt in, everyone... Would
you be willing to stay for dinner as
well?
129:
The truth is, I've wanted to talk to
you for a long time. You were such a
huge help to Luca during the matter
with his father.
132:
Um, thank you, mom, but we
wouldn't want to take up their time.
Plus I'm sure they wouldn't want to
trouble you with cooking all that
food!
137: Didn't that seem fishy to you?
141:
I mean... He's always been a bit...
catty like that. Pretending to be
unfriendly and distant when he
really isn't.
147:
Luca's mom and Marina look very
similar.
157:
Holy crap, Stella, you just took the
words right out of my mouth!
162:
Hmm, now that you mention it, I can
see the resemblance. Their
personalities are totally different,
though.
167: You shut your mouth this instant!
170: Why am I getting singled out here?!
173:
L-Luca? Aren't they your friends? You
always talk about Alk, after all—
176:
Ah, um, if we're going to be eating
together, we'll need way more
ingredients! Alk, please help me out
with the shopping!
185:
I apologize for my rudeness back
there.
189:
You don't look too happy about all of
this.
193:
No, it's just... There have been so
many things happening at the
same time, I'm a bit overwhelmed.
197:
You don't want to worry your mom,
right?
201:
Yes. She's still down in the dumps
about my father not being here. I'd
rather not remind her of all that.
209:
I want to get a handle on this power,
and fast. Despite all my research, I
haven't made much progress.
213:
Frankly, I'm embarrassed to meet
you again under such
circumstances.
217:
I understand you've got a lot on your
mind, but...
220:
If you use the resources you've got
at your disposal well, I'm sure things
will work out. You can count on us to
help you out too!
224:
Ugh... I hate when you say things like
that, Alk.
228:
Hey, I'm not exactly a huge fan of
everything you've said to me either!
232:
I'll talk to my mother about my
power. I'll tell her I might be able to
get it under control.
235:
I'd like to go with you. Can I count on
your assistance?
242:
But, there is one thing I'd like to ask
you first.
245:
About Marina, and how you're
always thinking about her. And
especially since she looks so much
like your mom—
251:
I'm sorry, mom. I need some time to
myself to figure things out. But don't
worry, I'll come back.
254:
I understand, dear. I'll find the
strength to deal with this myself. You
do whatever it is you need to, okay?
262:
I... need to be stronger too. And
cooler. Much cooler.
264:
Then, I can finally go and see you
again, Marina.
